Claims WHAT IS CLAIMED IS: An apparatus comprising: a carrier comprising collagen and configured to receive a radioactive a loader having: a first surface; an opposing second surface parallel to the first surface; a receiving surface between the first and second surfaces at first ends of each of the first surface and the second surfaces; a loading port at an entrance of a loading channel extending through the receiving surface of the loader, the loading port defining a first alignment interface on an outer surface of the receiving surface; and a loading bed between the first and second surfaces sized to support the carrier on the loading bed; an injection device having; an injection channel configured to contain a radioactive seed, the injection channel and the loading channel having substantially equal diameters; a distal end having a second alignment interface sized and shaped to engage with the first alignment interface of the loading port; and a plunger having a first end comprising a longitudinal rod extending at least partially within the injection channel and a second end outside of the injection channel configured for engagement by a 

 human operator in order to move the longitudinal rod within the injection channel; wherein with at least a portion of the injection device inserted into the loading port such that the first alignment interface engages the second alignment interface, the radioactive seed is movable out of the injection device into the collagen carrier on the loading bed in response to movement of the second end of the plunger towards the distal end of the injection device. 2. The apparatus of claim 1 , wherein the carrier comprises a top surface, a bottom surface, and a uniform thickness therebetween. 3. The apparatus of claim 1 , wherein the first end of the longitudinal rod has a diameter equal to a diameter of the injection channel. 4. The apparatus of claim 3, wherein an entire length of the longitudinal rod has a diameter equal to the diameter of the injection channel. 5. The apparatus of claim 1 , further comprising an injection plate at the first end of the plunger, the injection plate having a diameter equal to a diameter of the injection channel. 6. The apparatus of claim 1 , further comprising: a punch configured to create a guide channel in the carrier at a location of the carrier where the radioactive seed is inserted. 7. The apparatus of claim 1 , wherein the first and second alignment interfaces are non-linear and are shaped to engage one another such that the injection device is stabilized with reference to the loader when the first and second alignment interfaces are engaged. 8. The apparatus of claim 7, wherein the first and second alignment interfaces each include a single tier. 9. The apparatus of claim 7, wherein the first and second alignment interfaces each include two or more tiers. 10. The apparatus of claim 7, the loader further comprising: a second loading port through the receiving surface, the second loading port defining a second channel configured to receive the injection device. 1 1 . The apparatus of claim 7, wherein the loader further comprises a second loading port through the receiving surface and the injection device includes a second injection channel, wherein when the first and second alignment interfaces are engaged the second injection channel is aligned with the second loading port such that said pushing the second end of the plunger towards the distal end of the injection device cause a second radioactive seed within the second injection channel to move through the second loading port and into the carrier. 12. A method comprising: placing a collagen carrier onto a loading bed of a loader, the loader comprising: a first surface; an opposing second surface parallel to the first surface; a receiving surface between the first and second surfaces at first ends of each of the first surface and the second surfaces; a loading port defining an entrance of a loading channel extending through the receiving surface of the loader; and the loading bed between the first and second surfaces sized to support the collagen carrier; 

 providing an injection device having: an injection channel containing a radioactive seed; a distal end configured to engage with the loading port of the loader; and a plunger having a first end comprising a longitudinal rod extending at least partially within the injection channel and a second end outside of the injection channel; engaging the distal end of the injection device with the loading port of the loader such that central axes of the injection channel and the loading channel are substantially aligned; applying force, towards the loader, to the second end of the plunger causing movement of the longitudinal rod within the injection channel and, correspondingly, causing the first end of the plunger to move the radioactive seed towards the distal end of the injection device, out of the injection channel into the loading channel, and then into the collagen carrier within the loader; and applying force, away from the loader, to the second end of the plunger causing movement of the longitudinal rod out of the loading channel, leaving the radioactive seed embedded in the collagen carrier. 13. The method of claim 12, wherein the collagen carrier comprises a substantially rectangular shape with a substantially uniform thickness. 14. The method of claim 12, further comprising inserting a punch through the loading channel and into a portion of the collagen carrier at a location of the collagen carrier where the radioactive seed is inserted. 15. The method of claim 14, wherein the punch comprises a longitudinal portion having diameter substantially equal to a diameter of the loading channel. 16. The method of claim 15, wherein the punch comprises a punch engagement interface at an end of the longitudinal portion, the punch engagement interface configured to engage with a loader engagement interface defined by the loading port. 17. A method comprising: positioning a loader for insertion of a radioactive seed into a carrier positioned within the loader, the loader comprising: a substantially enclosed area in which the carrier is positioned; a loading channel extending through a surface of the loader such that the carrier is accessible from outside the substantially enclosed area of the loader through the loading channel; and a loader engagement interface at an entrance of the loading channel; providing an injection device having: an injection channel containing a radioactive seed; a distal end having an injection engagement interface configured to engage with the loader engagement interface; and a longitudinal rod extending at least partially within the injection channel; moving the injection device to engage the loader engagement interface with the injection engagement interface such that central axes of the injection channel and the loading channel are substantially aligned; 

 causing movement of the longitudinal rod within the injection channel and at least partially into the loading channel, the movement of the longitudinal rod causing movement of the radioactive seed towards the distal end of the injection device, out of the injection channel into the loading channel, and then into the carrier within the loader; and causing movement of the longitudinal rod out of the loading channel, leaving the radioactive seed embedded in the carrier. 18. The method of claim 17, wherein the carrier comprises collagen. 19. The method of claim 17, wherein the radioactive seed is embedded in a central region within the carrier.
